parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel seal can cause oil leaks, loss of braking control, and potentially lead to a fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the rear wheel
loss of braking control
especially on wet pavement
smoke coming from the wheel area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The catastrophic failure of the transmission can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially result in death.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected transmission failure
no warning signs or symptoms before the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manufacturing defect in the transfer case can cause vibration, loss of control, and damage to the 4WD system, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vibration in 4WD when accelerating
excessive metal on the transfer case magnetic drain plug.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation or chuggle issue can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Hesitation
bump
or chuggle when driving at speeds between 25-45 mph
light accelerator pedal tip-in or tip-out maneuver
transmission in 3rd gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the trailer brake system can cause a loss of control over the trailer, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The "Service trailer brake system" warning appears on the dashboard
the trailer brake information does not display on the dashboard
the electric trailer brakes cannot be manually engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Engine Vibration Causing Electrical Connector Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive engine vibration can cause electrical connectors to vibrate loose, leading to reduced power mode, loss of control, and potential damage to the engine and transmission.
symptoms: The vehicle runs in reduced power mode
the vehicle lurches forward uncontrollably
the transmission makes banging noises
the electrical connector at the injector vibrates loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Repair Parts for Safety Recalls
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of repair parts for safety recalls can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The parts to repair the vehicle are unavailable
the safety recall cannot be completed
the vehicle remains in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the keyless ignition system can cause the vehicle to start unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or injuries if the vehicle is not properly secured.
symptoms: The vehicle starts on its own
the radio turns on and off
the dashboard lights turn on and off
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear camera can reduce the driver's visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: The rear camera display is blurry
foggy
or distorted
making it difficult or impossible to see objects behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Exhaust Heat Damage to Towed Vehicles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive heat from the exhaust system can cause damage to towed vehicles, potentially leading to fires or other hazards.
symptoms: The exhaust heat melts or deforms fiberglass or plastic components on the towed vehicle
the towed vehicle is damaged or deformed
the risk of fire or other hazards is increased.
